snippet: New Zealand and South Africa both went into the often-transitional post-Rugby World Cup year needing to fill some big boots and while the All Blacks achieved it with barely a stutter, South Africa's 2016 turned into be an annus horribilis....
lead_paragraph: New Zealand and South Africa both went into the often-transitional post-Rugby World Cup year needing to fill some big boots and while the All Blacks achieved it with barely a stutter, South Africa's 2016 turned into be an annus horribilis.

headline.main: All Blacks Still Rule as Springboks Endure Year to Forget
